  "prompt": "What should my board exam percentage be to get admission to St. Xaviers in Kolkata for a BSC in mathematics? Does St. Xaviers consider only mathematics marks as criteria for admission?",
  "response": "To gain admission to St. Xavier's College in Kolkata for a Bachelor of Science (BSc) in Mathematics, the specific percentage required can vary each year depending on several factors, including the overall performance of applicants and the college's cutoff for that year. Generally, a high percentage\u2014often in the range of 85% or higher in your board exams\u2014might be expected, but it is important to check the most current information directly from the college's official website or contact their admissions office for precise details.\n\nSt. Xavier's College typically considers the overall percentage obtained in the qualifying examination (like the Class 12 board exams) rather than solely focusing on mathematics marks. However, they may have specific criteria or weightage for mathematics marks as the program is mathematics-focused. It's always best to consult the official admissions guidelines or contact the college to get the most accurate and detailed information.",
